## Public Member Functions

### dump() {#aa5aa3ab228a831a384f7a9c50bc648e4}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>void PDBSymbolBlock::dump (<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/pdb/pdbsymdumper">PDBSymDumper</a> &amp; Dumper) const</>}
  labels = {["virtual"]}>
Dumps the contents of a symbol a <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/raw-ostream">raw&#95;ostream</a>.

By default this will just call <a href="#aa5aa3ab228a831a384f7a9c50bc648e4">dump()</a> on the underlying RawSymbol, which allows us to discover unknown properties, but individual implementations of <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/pdb/pdbsymbol">PDBSymbol</a> may override the behavior to only dump known fields.
